---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
    <section style="padding-top: 60px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <span class="tag sanskrit">॥ कार्यम् कौशलम् ॥</span>
            <span class="tag">Digital Presence</span>
            <h1>Digital Presence <span class="highlight">Systems</span></h1>
            <p class="lead" style="max-width: 650px;">
                Build a professional digital presence that clearly communicates what you do, establishes credibility, and creates a structured path for qualified inquiries.
            </p>
            <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                <span style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--accent);">Starting at ₹25,000</span>
                <span style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--text-muted);">|</span>
                <span style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--text-muted);">Timeline: 2–4 Weeks</span>
            </div>
            <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-muted); border-left: 2px solid var(--accent-dim); padding-left: 1rem;">
                Systems Audit Included — Every Digital Presence engagement begins with a Systems Audit and Discovery Process to ensure implementation decisions are based on evidence rather than assumptions.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>A Digital Presence Is More Than A Website</h2>
            <p>Most professionals do meaningful work. However, their website, content, and online presence often fail to communicate that work clearly. Information becomes scattered. Content becomes difficult to maintain. Visitors struggle to understand what you do, who you help, and why it matters.</p>
            <p>The result is a digital presence that no longer reflects the quality of the work behind it. A Digital Presence System is designed to solve that problem.</p>
            <p>Instead of treating websites, content, and information as separate challenges, we create a structured system that helps your work become easier to understand, maintain, and grow over time.</p>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Common Problems</h2>
            <ul class="structural">
                <li>Your website has grown without a clear structure</li>
                <li>Your content feels scattered</li>
                <li>Visitors struggle to understand your work</li>
                <li>Navigation has become confusing</li>
                <li>Your website no longer reflects your current direction</li>
                <li>Knowledge is spread across multiple platforms</li>
                <li>Publishing feels inconsistent</li>
                <li>Growth has outpaced the systems supporting it</li>
            </ul>
            <p>If several of these problems sound familiar, the issue is often structural rather than visual.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>Who This Is For</h2>
            <p>This engagement is designed for:</p>
            <ul class="structural">
                <li>Consultants</li>
                <li>Educators</li>
                <li>Researchers</li>
                <li>Independent Professionals</li>
                <li>Founder-Led Businesses</li>
                <li>Knowledge Businesses</li>
                <li>Subject Matter Experts</li>
            </ul>
            <p>If your expertise is valuable but your online presence feels fragmented, difficult to maintain, or difficult to understand, this engagement may be a good fit.</p>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Why Digital Presence Problems Persist</h2>
            <p>Many people assume they need a new website. In reality, the website is often only the visible layer of the problem.</p>
            <p>Problems frequently originate from unclear positioning, poor information architecture, fragmented content, confusing navigation, or the absence of a sustainable content system. Improving design without improving structure often recreates the same problems later.</p>
            <p>This engagement focuses on the system behind the website rather than the website alone.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>What This Is Not</h2>
            <ul class="structural">
                <li>A template website package</li>
                <li>A redesign for the sake of redesign</li>
                <li>A collection of disconnected pages</li>
                <li>A one-time visual refresh</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Digital Presence Systems focus on structure, clarity, maintainability, and long-term usefulness.</p>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">What You'll Receive</h2>
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 1rem;">
                <div style="background: var(--surface); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">The Blueprint Layer</h3>
                    <ul style="list-style: none; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem;">
                        <li>• Digital Presence Audit</li>
                        <li>• Website Architecture</li>
                        <li>• Positioning Framework</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div style="background: var(--surface); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">The Operational Layer</h3>
                    <ul style="list-style: none; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem;">
                        <li>• Navigation Structure</li>
                        <li>• Content Framework</li>
                        <li>• Documentation Package</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h2 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Example Areas Of Work</h2>
            <ul class="structural">
                <li>Business Websites</li>
                <li>Consultant Websites</li>
                <li>Educational Platforms</li>
                <li>Resource Libraries</li>
                <li>Knowledge Hubs</li>
                <li>Documentation Systems</li>
                <li>Content Archives</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>How The Process Works</h2>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 2;">
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Step 1 — Systems Audit:</strong> Every project begins with a Systems Audit and Discovery Process.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Step 2 — Discovery & Planning:</strong> Goals, priorities, constraints, and opportunities are clarified.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Step 3 — Architecture Design:</strong> Website structure, navigation, content systems, and positioning frameworks are developed.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Step 4 — Implementation:</strong> Approved recommendations are implemented according to project scope.</li>
                <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Step 5 — Documentation & Handover:</strong> Documentation, guidance, and implementation notes are delivered.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="padding-top: 40px; border-bottom: none;">
        <div class="container reading" style="max-width: var(--container);">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem;">
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Do I need an existing website?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">No. The system can be designed whether you already have a website or are starting from scratch.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Will you build the website?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">When implementation is part of the approved scope, yes. However, the objective is not simply building a website. The objective is creating a digital presence that accurately represents the work behind it.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Can this work with WordPress?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">Yes. WordPress can be used when it is an appropriate fit for the project.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Is SEO included?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">SEO is considered as part of the overall digital presence system rather than treated as a separate activity.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.1rem;">Is every project accepted?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.95rem;">No. Projects are evaluated before engagement to ensure the goals, scope, and expected outcomes are an appropriate fit.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 2rem; background: var(--surface); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem;">Build On A Strong Foundation</h2>
                <p>Websites change. Platforms change. Content grows. A well-structured digital presence remains useful through those changes. Because we do not build systems based on assumptions, every implementation project begins with a Systems Audit.</p>
                <p style="font-style: italic; color: var(--accent);">For qualifying projects, the audit investment is credited toward the project scope.</p>
                <a href="/work-with-aman/systems-audit" class="btn" style="margin-top: 1rem;">Request a Systems Audit</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>